# Docusaurus Project Structure Guide

This project is a [Docusaurus](mdc:https:/docusaurus.io) documentation site. Here are the key parts of the structure:

## Main Configuration
- The main configuration is in [docusaurus.config.ts](mdc:docusaurus.config.ts).
- Sidebar configuration is in [sidebars.ts](mdc:sidebars.ts).
- TypeScript settings are in [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json).
- Project dependencies and scripts are in [package.json](mdc:package.json).

## Documentation
- All documentation markdown files are in the [docs/](mdc:docs) directory, organized in subfolders (e.g., [tutorial-basics/](mdc:docs/tutorial-basics), [tutorial-extras/](mdc:docs/tutorial-extras)).
- The main entry doc is [welcome.md](mdc:docs/welcome.md).
- The sidebar is autogenerated from the docs folder structure by default.

## Blog
- Blog posts are in the [blog/](mdc:blog) directory. Each post is a markdown or MDX file (e.g., [2019-05-28-first-blog-post.md](mdc:blog/2019-05-28-first-blog-post.md), [2021-08-01-mdx-blog-post.mdx](mdc:blog/2021-08-01-mdx-blog-post.mdx)).
- Blog post folders (e.g., [2021-08-26-welcome/](mdc:blog/2021-08-26-welcome)) can contain images and an index.md.
- Author and tag metadata are in [authors.yml](mdc:blog/authors.yml) and [tags.yml](mdc:blog/tags.yml).

## Static Assets
- Static files (images, favicon, etc.) are in [static/](mdc:static) and [static/img/](mdc:static/img).
- These are served at the root of the built site.

## Source Code
- Custom React components are in [src/components/](mdc:src/components), e.g., [HomepageFeatures/](mdc:src/components/HomepageFeatures).
- The main homepage is [src/pages/index.tsx](mdc:src/pages/index.tsx).
- Standalone markdown pages can be placed in [src/pages/](mdc:src/pages/markdown-page.md).
- Global CSS is in [src/css/custom.css](mdc:src/css/custom.css). Component-scoped CSS modules are in their respective folders (e.g., [styles.module.css](mdc:src/components/HomepageFeatures/styles.module.css)).

## Markdown Preferences
- **Always prefer markdown syntax over HTML** when possible (see [.cursorrules](mdc:.cursorrules) for detailed guidelines)
- Use markdown headers (`#`, `##`, `###`) instead of HTML tags
- Use markdown images (`![alt](mdc:url)`) instead of `<img>` tags
- Use markdown emphasis (`**bold**`, `*italic*`) instead of HTML tags
- Use horizontal rules (`---`) to separate sections
- Add emojis to headings for visual appeal when appropriate

## Development
- See [README.md](mdc:README.md) for setup, build, and deployment instructions.

---

**Tip:** To add new docs, place markdown files in [docs/](mdc:docs). For new blog posts, add markdown or MDX files to [blog/](mdc:blog). For custom pages, use [src/pages/](mdc:src/pages). For static assets, use [static/](mdc:static). Always prioritize markdown syntax for better readability and maintainability.
